  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "QAM8755 Safety shall cover ADAS/ADs and IVI functions"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "ADAS and ADS use cases"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Highway autopilot (HWP)",
        "Traffic jam assist",
        "Automatic emergency braking and lane keep assist",
        "Automated valet parking"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "IVI use cases"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Instrument cluster tell-tale icon display",
        "Surround view systems with object detection and free space estimation",
        "Rear view camera",
        "Driver monitoring system/occupant monitoring system",
        "e-Mirror"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Safe computing sub systems in QAM8775"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Application processor subsystem (APSS)",
        "Graphics processing unit (GPU)",
        "Safety island (SAIL)",
        "Neural signal processor (NSP)",
        "Computer vision processor (CVP)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Our focus here is on SAIL so we move towards SAIL safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "SAIL domain can achieve ASIL-D level whereas APSS can achieve up to ASIL-B"
    }
  ],
  "attachments": []
}